The {{nihongo|'''''Takanami'' class destroyer'''|<U+305F><U+304B><U+306A><U+307F><U+578B><U+8B77><U+885B><U+8266>|Takanami-gata goeikan}} is a class of [[Japan]]ese guided-missile and [[anti-submarine warfare|ASW]] [[destroyer]], entering service with the [[Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force]] (JMSDF) from 1998. 

==Description==
The ''Takanami''-class is a fourth generation post-war destroyer for the JMSDF, and is an evolution of the previous {{sclass|Murasame|destroyer|2}}. Major changes include an improved [[fire control system]] and [[Tactical Data Link|data link]], as well as a new [[sonar]] system. In terms of weaponry, the 3-inch gun on the ''Murasame'' has been replaced with a larger 127&nbsp;mm gun, and the older [[AIM-7 Sparrow|Sea Sparrow]] anti-air missile has been replaced by the new [[RIM-162 ESSM|''Evolved Sea Sparrow'' ESSM (RIM-162)]] missiles in a Mk-48VLS (Vertical Launch System). This changes have resulted in a larger hull displacement than the ''Murasame'' by about 100 tons.

All ships in the class are named for World War II destroyers.{{Citation needed|date=October 2010}}

